product_name: Yves Saint Laurent Black Opium Eau de Parfum Spray, Perfume for Women, 3.0 oz
review_text:
Black Opium Eau de Parfum is a captivating fragrance that perfectly balances boldness and sensuality. From the moment I sprayed it, I was enveloped in a warm, inviting aroma that felt both daring and glamorous.

The top notes of coffee and pink pepper create a vibrant opening‚Äîbold yet not overpowering. The coffee adds a unique twist, giving the perfume its signature intensity. As it settles, the heart notes of orange blossom and jasmine add a touch of femininity, creating a beautifully floral and creamy mid-layer.

Finally, the base notes of vanilla, patchouli, and cedar deliver a sweet and earthy finish. The vanilla adds warmth, while the patchouli and cedar provide depth, making this scent long-lasting and luxurious.

Black Opium is perfect for evening wear, romantic dinners, or anytime you want to feel confident and magnetic. It's not for the faint-hearted but rather for those who love to make a statement. The bottle design, with its glittery black exterior, mirrors the fragrance's glamorous and edgy vibe.

If you're someone who enjoys rich, warm, and slightly sweet perfumes with a unique twist, Black Opium is a must-try. It's a timeless scent that has become a staple in my collection.

product_name: Yves Saint Laurent Black Opium Eau de Parfum Spray, Perfume for Women, 3.0 oz
review_text:

Plus, the longevity is amazing! (I'm using the EDP.) Even after a long day, the fragrance remains fresh on my pulse points.
If you love simple and soothing fragrances, this is perfect for you.‚ù§Ô∏è

Thank you, YSL‚Äîthis will be a forever purchase for me! ü•∞

product_name: Yves Saint Laurent Black Opium Eau de Parfum Spray, Perfume for Women, 3.0 oz
review_text:
Black Opium Eau De Parfum is truly one of my all-time favorite perfumes, and receiving it as a gift from my husband on Christmas morning made my day absolutely perfect!

The scent is luxurious, seductive, and incredibly captivating. It has the perfect balance of rich coffee, warm vanilla, and sweet floral notes, creating a fragrance that is both bold and feminine. I feel confident and elegant every time I wear it, and it always draws compliments wherever I go.

The packaging is stunning and adds to the overall experience of the perfume‚Äîit's as beautiful as the fragrance inside.

I couldn't be happier with this thoughtful gift, and I know it will remain a staple in my collection for years to come. If you're looking for a perfume that feels special and empowering, Black Opium is it!

review_text: Gucci Bloom is a popular fragrance from the luxury fashion house Gucci, known for its rich floral scent. Here's an overview of the Gucci Bloom fragrance:  ### Key Features - **Type:** Eau de Parfum - **Launch Year:** 2017 - **Perfumer:** Alberto Morillas - **Fragrance Family:** Floral  ### Scent Profile - **Top Notes:** There are no traditional top notes in Gucci Bloom, which contributes to its immediately impactful and enduring floral presence. - **Heart Notes:**    - **Rangoon Creeper (Chinese honeysuckle):** A unique floral note with a slightly powdery finish.   - **Jasmine Bud Extract:** Offers a fresh, green, and petal-like scent.   - **Tuberose:** Provides a rich, creamy, and seductive floral aroma.  ### Packaging - **Bottle Design:**    - **Shape:** Simple, square-shaped bottle.   - **Color:** Soft pink lacquered glass with a minimalist design.   - **Label:** Ivory label with black Gucci logo and text.  ### Usage - **Application:** Apply to pulse points such as wrists, neck, and behind the ears for long-lasting wear. - **Occasions:** Suitable for both daytime and evening wear, perfect for spring and summer due to its fresh and vibrant floral notes.  ### Benefits - **Longevity:** Offers good longevity, typically lasting several hours. - **Sillage:** Moderate sillage, leaving a pleasant trail without being overpowering. - **Versatility:** A versatile fragrance suitable for various occasions, from casual outings to formal events.  ### Considerations - **Personal Preference:** As with all perfumes, it's best to try a sample before purchasing to ensure it suits your personal taste and skin chemistry. - **Storage:** Store in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight to preserve the fragrance.  ### Availability - **Retail:** Available at high-end department stores, specialty fragrance boutiques, and online retailers. - **Price:** Positioned in the premium price range, reflecting the luxury brand and high-quality ingredients.

product_name: Gucci Bloom Eau De Parfum, Perfume for Women, 3.3 Oz
review_text: MIX PERFUME Famous fashion brand Gucci has just launched the new perfume Gucci Bloom in August 2017, the first perfume at the hands of creator Alesxandro Michele..  Jasmine extract, obtained through a proprietary method of copper extraction to impart a fresh green and chamomile scent on the skin.  Rangoon creeper, which represents the concept and name of the perfume, the gentle powdery floral scent captured as the flower blooms from white and gradually darkens to pink, then red.  A scent designed to celebrate the authenticity, vitality and diversity of women, evolving in a natural, personally expressive way. Blended by master perfumer Alberto Morillas under the direction of Gucci's Creative Director. Gucci Bloom is created to open like its namesake, capturing the rich scent of a vibrant garden filled with an abundance of flowers. Tuberose and jasmine combined with iris root or Rangoon Creeper ‚Äì a unique flower discovered in South India that is being used for the first time in perfumery to create a scent The unique scent takes users to an imaginary garden. Brand: Gucci Concentration: Eau de Parfum (EDP) Perfume type: Women Typical scent: jasmine sambac, tuberose, orris root, honeysuckle.

product_name: Gucci Bloom Eau De Parfum, Perfume for Women, 3.3 Oz
review_text: Beautiful Jasmin scent that's captivating and huge compliment getter. The scent leaves a strong sillage where people approach me to ask what I'm wearing! Absolutely love the bottle it feels sturdy in my hands and color is lovely. Will be repurchasing once I run out and will remain in my collection forever. product_name: Viktor & Rolf Flowerbomb Perfume for Women Mini Gift Set
review_text:
This perfume is a really interesting mix of floral, musk and citrus notes.

It is called flower bomb for a reason. There is a rich mix of floral scents such as Jasmine, Rose, Orchid and Freesia. 

Alongside this a zesty fresh scent of bergamont and green tea.

And underlying it all, musk and Patchouli make this a rich and warm scent despite the stereotypically fresh notes on top.

It's a really gorgeous feminine scent that wraps you in warmth and adds something a little bit different to an otherwise pretty scent and feels somehow womanly.

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Cherry Baby Eau de Parfum Fragrance for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text: Bummed‚Ä¶Admittedly I'm a fan of the Caramel Dream (which seems to be in the minority) and haven't smelled Sweet Tooth yet (which seems to be the overwhelming favorite) and was excited to try this cherries, chocolate and musky scent (granted these are supposed to be some of the top, middle and base notes) based off of my love for Caramel Dream and newly found love for cherry scented (not the fake overly sweet style, but deeper richer and/or tart or mix of) and curious allure of the chocolate and musk mixed with cherries. It isn't a bad smelling scent, but is not what I hoped for or expected and actually kind of smells ‚Äúcheap‚Äù and while $30/ounce isn't expensive, but personally it isn't worth the price and doesn't live up to Caramel Dreams. It's fine and smells good, but longevity and sillage is weak (it's very much a close skin scent) and cherries and chocolate aren't coming through much for me. Sadly, you would be better off getting Guess Seductive Red or Fine'ry Not Another Cherry if you're looking for an affordable cherry (not chocolate or really musk scent though) scented perfume. Also would layer with cherry scented body spray and lotion (both Guess and Fine'ry make matching body sprays and you MIGHT find body lotion from Guess? OR Bath and Body Works has cherry options too‚Äîhaven't tried them yet though) to deepen and help with longevity and sillage. Hope this helps. I can't justify the price or afford Tom Ford's Lost Cherry and now that I know I love a good cherry scent, I'm on the hunt for affordable quality dupes! Also maybe research and see what you can find elsewhere, but know you could be throwing away $ and if it seems too good to be true, then it is and be forewarned. Hoping someone makes what I'm on the hunt for that is both affordable and has the longevity and sillage I seek (in a large bottle lol) soon/in time for autumn/winter!!!!

review_text:
I recently picked up a fragrance from Walmart, and I have to say, it's a great find for those seeking a premium scent without breaking the bank. The scent is truly amazing and has a high-end feel to it. Every time I use it, I often receive compliments, which is always a nice confidence boost. It's versatile enough to fit seamlessly into my daily routine. I typically apply it in the morning before heading to the gym to stay fresh during my workout, and I reapply it after to ensure I don't reek. It's also great for wearing when going out later in the day, whether you're meeting friends or running errands.

One downside, however, is that the scent doesn't last very long‚Äîabout two to three hours‚Äîso it requires reapplication if you want it to last throughout the day. Despite this, the fragrance offers an excellent balance of quality and affordability. If you're looking for a product that gives you a premium vibe without the hefty price tag, this is a solid choice. It's definitely worth the money, especially for everyday use.

product_name: Jean Paul Gaultier Le Male Elixir Parfum 2.5 OZ
review_text: The item received was counterfeit.  Upon opening it from 3rd party seller it was not in secure packaging and had obvious defects like denting and paint flaking.  Nozzle was wrong size and the outer can had incorrect number of rings at top and the nozzle secure pin was the wrong size and poorly made, all signs of counterfeit product.  Product was returned and Walmart advised of counterfeit product.  It should be noted that this product was compared directly to an authenticated real product to confirm the counterfeit discrepancies.  I would not recommend any future frangrance purchases through Walmart unless they can guarantee authenticity with their 3rd party vendors.

product_name: Jean Paul Gaultier Le Male Elixir Parfum 2.5 OZ

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: I had saw reviews of this perfume on TikTok, and I was unsure if I would like it. I have to say this perfume smells amazing. It is light with a hint of vanilla with a long lasting scent. It's very versatile and can be worn every day or for those special occasions. Many reviews say it smells like YSL black opium, which I have never actually smelled, but I have seen the price tag of, and I have to say for this price you cannot beat it. A little bit goes a long way and when I wear it, I get multiple compliments.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: This is by far my favorite perfume. I have tried designer brands, dupes, and off brands and this one is AMAZING. It smells luxurious and you can smell each note separately but combined is magic. I get asked frequently what I'm wearing and people are surprised when I tell them how much it costs. It smells expensive and the lasts for several hours. This is the only perfume I will buy!

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text:
I wasn't too fond of this scent at first... It smelled too mature for me and I thought it was going to be sweet, but it's not exactly gourmand sweet. After letting this sit for months, I used it again and loved it!!! The dry down is so warm and cozy and the pink pepper kind of fades away, which is what I think I disliked most about it. 

It's a beautiful scent that lasts several hours. Let it sit on the shelf for a while to mature.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: This perfume was a blind purchase for me and it's to die for. It smells very musky, cedar wood, and clean at first but when it dried down you can still smell the cedar wood but it's not as strong compared to the vanilla and coffee scent. It's a very warm fragrance that smells clean and simple. It's definitely worth it.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: I have worn the original YSL Black Opium and have been wearing dossier's version for years but it doesn't last as long as it used to when I purchased it in previous years. I now need to apply it twice or more for it to last all day on my skin, which I don't remember needing to do in previous years

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: Love the perfume but it isn't a warm/vanilla scent that I was expecting due to the name of the perfume being ambery vanilla. It's very floral and smells exactly like their other perfume called fruity brown sugar. If you're looking for a warm scent don't buy this perfume. Still giving it 4 stars though because it does smell nice and lasts long it's just not what I expected or wanted.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text:
It's a nice scent, but quite overrated. I find it more feminine and floral than black opium which is problematic for me as floral scents do not complement my natural scent. 
The price is good, however the scent does not last the whole day. 
Overall, it's not a bad purchase, but it just doesn't work for me.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: I have bought this scent prior, and I love it! But for some reason the batch I received does not smell the same. I am not sure if it changed recipes or if it's just a bad batch. It also is not staying on as long. I used to be able to use it in the morning and still smell it on myself after my work day. A little disappointed and might not purchase again just because it's too expensive with shipping and fees to not have consistency within the fragrances.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: I'm sorry but no. I dislike how expensive the department store Designer fragrances are, but these knock-offs are not comparable. They remind me of dollar store fragrances from the 90s. Too much alcohol, and when the alcohol finally wears off the strength of the fragrances is comparable to after a 8 hr work day, and you can only smell it if you are hugging . So to be frank, I respect the quality of products when they stay in their lane and don't try and make themselves out to be comparable to a higher quality item, otherwise they are setting themselves up for failure.

review_text: Even though I am not a fan of this musician, my daughter likes somw of her music. This perfume supersingly smells really good. Not too strong and no flowery tones to it at all. Just a small amount goes far and lasts a long time. If you dont like floral tones, I would recommend this perfume.

product_name: Ariana Grande Sweet Like Candy Eau De Parfum, 1.0 oz
review_text: Ariana Grande's "Sweet Like Candy" parfum is a delightful fragrance that captures a youthful and playful spirit. With top notes of juicy berries and sugar-frosted Italian bergamot, the scent opens with a sweet, fruity burst. The heart notes of fluffy marshmallow and jasmine add a creamy, floral depth, while the base notes of vanilla and cashmere wood provide a warm, lasting finish. The bottle's design, featuring a cute pink pom-pom, complements the fun and flirty essence of the perfume. It's a great choice for those who enjoy sweet, gourmand fragrances that are both light and enchanting, perfect for daily wear or special occasions.

product_name: Ariana Grande Sweet Like Candy Eau De Parfum, 1.0 oz
review_text: I was looking for a new perfume. The bottle was cute and the pink fuzzy ball was appealing to me. One whiff from the tester bottle and I was hooked! It is a soft, sweet scent that stays with you but is not overpowering. I love it and have been sporting this scent for about five years.

product_name: Ariana Grande Sweet Like Candy Eau De Parfum, 1.0 oz
review_text: I love the smell, it is very sweet, but subtle. You can't go wrong with this fragrance. It's not overpowering, but it leaves a hint of sweetness.

product_name: Ariana Grande Sweet Like Candy Eau De Parfum, 1.0 oz

I like moonlight and cloud better than this one. It's not bad but not great. A big let down was the bottle doesn't function as I thought. product_name: Lancome Miracle Eau De Parfum Spray for Women 3.4 oz
review_text:
I am a twenty year old girl who is obsessed with purchasing amazing perfumes. A few months back I bought La Vie Est Belle Iris Absolu and it has become my favorite. However, I recently purchased Miracle, and it has quickly become one of my favorite fragrances. This high-end perfume offers a delicate floral scent that is both sophisticated and understated. 
The initial notes are a gentle blend of jasmine and magnolia, which provide a fresh and airy floral aroma. As it settles, hints of rose and ginger emerge, adding depth without overpowering the senses. The base notes of white musk and a touch of sandalwood give it a creamy, smooth finish that lingers softly on the skin.
One of the standout features of this perfume is its longevity. Despite its subtlety, it lasts throughout the day, requiring only a light touch-up if transitioning from day to evening.
The sillage is perfect for those who prefer a more intimate scent. It stays close to the skin, creating a personal aura rather than a cloud of fragrance. This makes it ideal for both professional settings and social gatherings where you want to make a gentle impression.

review_text: Miracle Eau de Parfum is a beautifully balanced fragrance that captures the spirit of hope and positivity. product_name: Lancome Miracle Eau De Parfum Spray for Women 3.4 oz
review_text: I would give this zero stars if I could! I NEVER give anything a negative review, as I usually just let it go, deciding that it was just my particular product that was bad, and everyone/company deserves a second chance. HOWEVER, the seller completely ripped me off. I finally received my package, only to find out the bottle has been filled with a mysterious substance. This is certainly not the high quality Miracle perfume I've known for years. Anytime you spray Miracle on, it stays on until you shower again. This mysterious substance wears off in less than an hour. It smells and looks watered down. Despite having read the bad reviews over the last month, I decided to go ahead and take a chance and order it. Don't do what I did and waste your time and money. It's very disappointing that people will try to scam you during the holiday season. Not to count, it's very disappointing that Walmart would continue to approve a third party seller who has continuous bad reviews with packages not showing up and mysterious substances in bottles. This is not the first nor last time they're going to rip people off. Do yourself a favor and order directly from a company and not a third party. Also, when a $100   bottle of perfume is ‚Äúon sale‚Äú for less than $40, that's probably a red flag you should pay attention to! Ugh!

product_name: Drakkar Noir by Guy Laroche Eau de Toilette Spray Fragrance for Men, 6.7 oz
review_text: This is a scent that will linger on you for hours on end. I was totally unfamiliar with Drakkar Noir by Guy Laroche. When I use a men's fragrance, it's usually cedar, vetiver based. Currently, I have Le Vetiver by Carven , Vetiver Extreme by Guerlain, Vetyver by Malizia Uomo and Royall Vetiver. They are woodsy and mannish when used very sparingly. The Drakkar Noir by Guy Laroche, in my opinion, would seem more likely feminine than masculine, if there is some type of distinction of fragrances.  When I use my favorites, I usually dilute them with wet hands. I want just a trace aroma. The Drakkar Noir by Guy Laroche, for me, will require considerable dilution. I sparayed a bit on my bare hand and the scent lingered for almost three days.

review_text: After reading many reviews I ended up purchasing this scent as a Christmas present for my brother and he absolutely loves it! It is the perfect scent for anyone that doesn't like an overbearing musky man-smell. The fruity twist really comes through to soften up the woodsy notes.

product_name: Dossier Aromatic Pineapple Eau De Parfum, Inspired by Ysl's Y, Cologne for Men, 1.7 oz
review_text: My grandson had reminded me that I bought this sent a couple years ago. I forgot he saved the bottle. So 2024 Christmas he received it and he was so happy and I added another scent also and he just kept smelling the cap. I will be buying more next year for the men in my life.

product_name: Dossier Aromatic Pineapple Eau De Parfum, Inspired by Ysl's Y, Cologne for Men, 1.7 oz
review_text: It pays to smell good , along side of great ! Hygiene, and of course , a good smelling perfume definitely adds to just that,this scent simply speaks of its title‚Ä¶Thanks again dossier :)

product_name: Dossier Aromatic Pineapple Eau De Parfum, Inspired by Ysl's Y, Cologne for Men, 1.7 oz
review_text: Absolutely love the smell, It has a fresh but almost fruity scent. I will say it does not smell like pineapple at all hardly but it still smells amazing. Definitely recommend.

product_name: Dossier Aromatic Pineapple Eau De Parfum, Inspired by Ysl's Y, Cologne for Men, 1.7 oz
review_text: This is the best economical version out there. It's perfect for lounging and daily wear. I use the EDP for special events of course, but this fills in nicely on the daily when you still wanna smell fresh and clean but don't wanna burn the more pricier bottle. Actually purchasing two more as I leave this review. Get it, you won't regret it.

product_name: Dossier Aromatic Pineapple Eau De Parfum, Inspired by Ysl's Y, Cologne for Men, 1.7 oz
review_text: Normally citrus is the only fruity note I like, but this is the right note of sweet. A true summer hit! Wear to the beach, or a night out. It feels chameleonic in its ability to be worn in different contexts, while never feeling out of place. Highly recommend.

product_name: Dossier Aromatic Pineapple Eau De Parfum, Inspired by Ysl's Y, Cologne for Men, 1.7 oz
review_text: This fragrance claims to be inspired by YSL's Y. I personally have not tried YSL's version but I LOVE Dossier's version because it is a great summer smell. It is sweet and subtle. I get compliments at work when I wear it and I do a very tough job where I sweat all day. I get asked how is it that I smell sweet although I'm working hard. The scent lasts at least 10hrs which is great. I notice that it's even better worn at night on a date night! Great job Dossier!

product_name: Dossier Aromatic Pineapple Eau De Parfum, Inspired by Ysl's Y, Cologne for Men, 1.7 oz
review_text: First off: this smells awesome - but it is false advertising. I don't get any of the top notes, most noticeably the pineapple. It also definitely a Man fragrance and not something I would ever wear myself.

product_name: Dossier Aromatic Pineapple Eau De Parfum, Inspired by Ysl's Y, Cologne for Men, 1.7 oz
review_text: I have purchased about 5 different scents over the years ‚Ä¶ this ine last pretty well compare to others ‚Ä¶.

review_text: Still discovering which notes we like to wear, so got this for my husband as it was a popular scent for men. Not sure what the original smells like, but he had to use for it to be noticable. This one was a miss for us.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: This is my favorite smell. This one did have a different color from the original bottle that I purchased maybe a year ago and there was a slight scent difference but nothing too crazy off. The first bottle I have does smell a little Better than this new last purchase. Not sure if the difference is because of time and aging or because the formula was changed.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: I had saw reviews of this perfume on TikTok, and I was unsure if I would like it. I have to say this perfume smells amazing. It is light with a hint of vanilla with a long lasting scent. It's very versatile and can be worn every day or for those special occasions. Many reviews say it smells like YSL black opium, which I have never actually smelled, but I have seen the price tag of, and I have to say for this price you cannot beat it. A little bit goes a long way and when I wear it, I get multiple compliments.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: This is by far my favorite perfume. I have tried designer brands, dupes, and off brands and this one is AMAZING. It smells luxurious and you can smell each note separately but combined is magic. I get asked frequently what I'm wearing and people are surprised when I tell them how much it costs. It smells expensive and the lasts for several hours. This is the only perfume I will buy!

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text:
I wasn't too fond of this scent at first... It smelled too mature for me and I thought it was going to be sweet, but it's not exactly gourmand sweet. After letting this sit for months, I used it again and loved it!!! The dry down is so warm and cozy and the pink pepper kind of fades away, which is what I think I disliked most about it. 

It's a beautiful scent that lasts several hours. Let it sit on the shelf for a while to mature.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: This perfume was a blind purchase for me and it's to die for. It smells very musky, cedar wood, and clean at first but when it dried down you can still smell the cedar wood but it's not as strong compared to the vanilla and coffee scent. It's a very warm fragrance that smells clean and simple. It's definitely worth it.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: I have worn the original YSL Black Opium and have been wearing dossier's version for years but it doesn't last as long as it used to when I purchased it in previous years. I now need to apply it twice or more for it to last all day on my skin, which I don't remember needing to do in previous years

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: Love the perfume but it isn't a warm/vanilla scent that I was expecting due to the name of the perfume being ambery vanilla. It's very floral and smells exactly like their other perfume called fruity brown sugar. If you're looking for a warm scent don't buy this perfume. Still giving it 4 stars though because it does smell nice and lasts long it's just not what I expected or wanted.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text:
It's a nice scent, but quite overrated. I find it more feminine and floral than black opium which is problematic for me as floral scents do not complement my natural scent. 
The price is good, however the scent does not last the whole day. 
Overall, it's not a bad purchase, but it just doesn't work for me.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: I have bought this scent prior, and I love it! But for some reason the batch I received does not smell the same. I am not sure if it changed recipes or if it's just a bad batch. It also is not staying on as long. I used to be able to use it in the morning and still smell it on myself after my work day. A little disappointed and might not purchase again just because it's too expensive with shipping and fees to not have consistency within the fragrances.

product_name: Dossier Ambery Vanilla Eau de Parfum, Inspired by YSL's Black Opium, Perfume for Women, 1.7 oz
review_text: I'm sorry but no. I dislike how expensive the department store Designer fragrances are, but these knock-offs are not comparable. They remind me of dollar store fragrances from the 90s. Too much alcohol, and when the alcohol finally wears off the strength of the fragrances is comparable to after a 8 hr work day, and you can only smell it if you are hugging . So to be frank, I respect the quality of products when they stay in their lane and don't try and make themselves out to be comparable to a higher quality item, otherwise they are setting themselves up for failure.

product_name: Lancome Miracle Eau De Parfum Spray for Women 3.4 oz
review_text:
I am a twenty year old girl who is obsessed with purchasing amazing perfumes. A few months back I bought La Vie Est Belle Iris Absolu and it has become my favorite. However, I recently purchased Miracle, and it has quickly become one of my favorite fragrances. This high-end perfume offers a delicate floral scent that is both sophisticated and understated. 
The initial notes are a gentle blend of jasmine and magnolia, which provide a fresh and airy floral aroma. As it settles, hints of rose and ginger emerge, adding depth without overpowering the senses. The base notes of white musk and a touch of sandalwood give it a creamy, smooth finish that lingers softly on the skin.
One of the standout features of this perfume is its longevity. Despite its subtlety, it lasts throughout the day, requiring only a light touch-up if transitioning from day to evening.
The sillage is perfect for those who prefer a more intimate scent. It stays close to the skin, creating a personal aura rather than a cloud of fragrance. This makes it ideal for both professional settings and social gatherings where you want to make a gentle impression.

product_name: Lancome Miracle Eau De Parfum Spray for Women 3.4 oz
review_text: I would give this zero stars if I could! I NEVER give anything a negative review, as I usually just let it go, deciding that it was just my particular product that was bad, and everyone/company deserves a second chance. HOWEVER, the seller completely ripped me off. I finally received my package, only to find out the bottle has been filled with a mysterious substance. This is certainly not the high quality Miracle perfume I've known for years. Anytime you spray Miracle on, it stays on until you shower again. This mysterious substance wears off in less than an hour. It smells and looks watered down. Despite having read the bad reviews over the last month, I decided to go ahead and take a chance and order it. Don't do what I did and waste your time and money. It's very disappointing that people will try to scam you during the holiday season. Not to count, it's very disappointing that Walmart would continue to approve a third party seller who has continuous bad reviews with packages not showing up and mysterious substances in bottles. This is not the first nor last time they're going to rip people off. Do yourself a favor and order directly from a company and not a third party. Also, when a $100   bottle of perfume is ‚Äúon sale‚Äú for less than $40, that's probably a red flag you should pay attention to! Ugh!

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Sweet Tooth Caramel Dream Eau De Parfum for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text:
The scent is not overpowering, but it's long-lasting and lingers just the right amount‚Äîperfect for daily wear or special occasions.
 Every time I wear this perfume, I get compliments on how amazing I smell. If you're a fan of sweet, gourmand fragrances, this is a must-try!
Caramel Dream is a deliciously charming scent that I can't get enough of. Highly recommend to anyone looking for a warm, inviting fragrance that feels as good as it smells!

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Sweet Tooth Caramel Dream Eau De Parfum for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text:
At first I thought it smelled kinda old lady-ish but after wearing it a few times
wooooow it's good. It's sweet, musky, sugary, and the tiniest bit powdery but not in a bad way. I've repurchased it twice already. The other scents by Sabrina Carpenter smell delicious too, the pink one (sweet tooth) is a little more juvenile and musky vs this ones (caramel dream) sophistication, and the newest one (cherry baby) is very much like cherry cough syrup while holding that same true musk note as the others. All equally addictive if you wear them a few times, but caramel dream is easily my favorite!

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Sweet Tooth Caramel Dream Eau De Parfum for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text: As a woman in my early twenties I've been in a in between with my signature scent. I don't want to smell like my mother, but I don't want to wear the same overly fruity scents I wore in High School either. I am happy to say I found the scent that is the perfect blend of sweet (youthful) and sophisticated (mature). This perfume will have you feeling and smelling like a snack. It is deeply alluring and rich. I have a feeling I will be wearing this for the remainder of my twenties. GET THIS PERFUME!

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Sweet Tooth Caramel Dream Eau De Parfum for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text: Originally, I didn't even plan on getting this one due to the caramel undertones, but whenever I did a pick up order, it got substituted. Honestly, I'm happy it did! It is subtly sweet, but still has a dark chocolatey undertone with a bit of orange. Highly recommend even for someone that doesn't like caramel that much. The scent is strong but not overpowering perfect for everyday

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Sweet Tooth Caramel Dream Eau De Parfum for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text:
Smells wonderful and is perfect for fall or winter. It smells like creamy caramel, but it also has an almost smoky depth to it after a few hours. It smells much more expensive than it is, and while the sillage isn't big, the scent lasts all day, and lasts longer on clothes.

I also like trying to layer this scent with other gourmand scents. So far, it's very versatile.

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Sweet Tooth Caramel Dream Eau De Parfum for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text: I love it but.. the box was opened already which is concerning since it goes on my skin.. other than that I love it. Smells like the original with more spice.. spicy, marshmallowy, floral..it's good but I still prefer the original.. they both have the cutest bottles though!

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Sweet Tooth Caramel Dream Eau De Parfum for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text:
4.5/5 I really didn't know which SC fragrance to try out first but based on a mix of the descriptions/reviews I went with the Caramel Dream. I'm not usually a fan of overly sweet smells, or perfumes with musk, so I was a little nervous. Thankfully, it's perfect. The scent has so many layers and is so stimulating. It's truly unique, captivating almost because it just invites you to keep smelling it just to catch all the different notes. 

My only complaint is that it's subtle. Not as subtle and evasive as a body spray, but this is definitely one of the weakest bottles of perfume in my current collection. I use more of this on my spray points than others in an effort to get it to the intensity level I want. It also doesn't seem to linger for long on skin or clothing. One application would get me through a dinner, but if I was wanting to wear it all day at the office I would definitely be doing a mid-day respritz. Just something to think about with the $30/oz price point--it's going to deplete faster than other 1 oz bottles.

product_name: Sabrina Carpenter Sweet Tooth Caramel Dream Eau De Parfum for Women, 30ml/1oz
review_text: This is the perfect combination of sweetness and sophistication. It smells so so good, and on scent alone it's 5 stars easy. Unfortunately, the scent fades incredibly fast as if it were a body spray (for me at least.) For the price I don't mind having to re-apply throughout the day though

product_name: ($124 Value) Yves Saint Laurent Mon Paris Eau De Parfum Spray, Perfume For Women, 3.0 Oz
review_text: I have a ph that tends to absorb fragrances and denatures them. I end up smelling different from anything in the bottle. I am also very sensitive to certain scents and end up with a headache. That said, Mon Paris is a floral scent that is a bit sweeter than Libre (which I can't stand) and is a bit gentler on my olfactory. The scent dies out mid away through the day but I can still get whiff here and there. I describe it as being a heavier floral, maybe tending towards lilies but not enough to overpower the sweeter notes. Which is something that I like about this fragrance, as I also am not fond of lilies. Basically, I am someone who has never bought perfume because I am so complicated and it took taking a chance on just the name to find a winner. Reviewing a scent is difficult but I feel that if you like a slightly sophisticated, playful floral, this one is probably for you.

It's also just as long lasting as Lancome's spray because whatever I wore the day before still smells like it. Definitely check it out! $30 for this perfume compared to $100  for a tiny bottle of Lancome is absolutely worth it even if you hate it lol regift it to someone else!

review_text: [This review was collected as part of a promotion.] Baccarat Rouge 540 is like a little treasure in a chic, gold-accented bottle‚Äîelegant and totally display-worthy. The scent? review_text:
[This review was collected as part of a promotion.] There have been quite a few unexpected changes to the E Elizabeth Arden scented range even though this is a good thing for Elizabeth Arden range, it left me feeling confused about which green tea scented product was my most favourite & trusted scent I often go back to after a time out. The packaging has changed & there are many other scents under this label all indicating the same thing only with different coloured packaging. The original green tea packaging was all light green & has a slightly more lemon scented hue to it, Which to me is refreshing during the summer season. This new green tea packaging is white on one side & green on the other, which was confusing & left me thinking that Elizabeth Arden no longer make my most favourite summer fragrance. Apparently this new display in colour packaging is the one I'm looking for & after purchasing A found that there is a slight variation in the way it smells, scent has less of this lemon tint to it & a hit of something else that I can't quite explain, maybe a slight earthy tone‚Ä¶ 
I have both on at this minute, on other wrist, so that I might be able to explain what this difference in the scent is ‚Ä¶ 
the difference' are so subtle, yet somehow quite obvious ‚Ä¶ 
I would so love to see original recipe return ..
